	\arrow[""{name=3, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "u", shift left=3, curve={height=-6pt}, from=1-5, to=1-7]
	\arrow["\alpha", Rightarrow, from=1, to=0]
	\arrow["\gamma", Rightarrow, from=3, to=2]
\end{tikzcd}\]
is given by
\[\begin{tikzcd}
	A && B && C & {=} & A && C
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "f", shift left=3, curve={height=-6pt}, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "g"', curve={height=6pt}, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow[""{name=2, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "u", shift left=3, curve={height=-6pt}, from=1-3, to=1-5]
	\arrow[""{name=3, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "v"', curve={height=6pt}, from=1-3, to=1-5]
	\arrow[""{name=4, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "uf", shift left=3, curve={height=-6pt}, from=1-7, to=1-9]
	\arrow[""{name=5, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "vg"', curve={height=6pt}, from=1-7, to=1-9]
	\arrow["\alpha", Rightarrow, from=0, to=1]
	\arrow["\gamma", Rightarrow, from=2, to=3]
	\arrow["{{\gamma * \alpha}}", Rightarrow, from=4, to=5]
\end{tikzcd}\]
where the composite $\gamma * \alpha$ is also denoted $\gamma \alpha : uf \Rightarrow vg$. Note that this also defines a category with objects 1-morphisms and morphisms 2-morphisms, where the identities are 
\[\begin{tikzcd}
	A && A
	\arrow[curve={height=6pt}, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{{\text{id}_A}}"', curve={height=6pt}, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "{{\text{id}_A}}", shift left=3, curve={height=-6pt}, from=1-1, to=1-3]
